Step-by-Step Setup Instructions
Step 1: Create Project Structure
bash# Navigate to Desktop
cd ~/Desktop

# Create main folder
mkdir AI_andreas
cd AI_andreas
Step 2: Create the Python File
bash# Create the file
touch AI_andreas.py

# Open it with default text editor
open -e AI_andreas.py
Now copy the code from the artifact into the opened file and save (CMD + S)
Step 3: Create Virtual Environment
bash# Make sure you're in the AI_andreas folder
cd ~/Desktop/AI_andreas

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv

# Activate virtual environment
source venv/bin/activate

# Your terminal should now show: (venv) user@macbook AI_andreas %
Step 4: Install Dependencies
bash# With virtual environment activated, install packages
pip install streamlit ollama

# Verify installation
pip list
Step 5: Setup Ollama
Method 1: Direct Download (RECOMMENDED)
bash# Open download page
open https://ollama.com/download/mac

Download the Ollama app
Open the .dmg or .zip file
Drag Ollama to Applications folder
Open Ollama from Applications (it will run in background)
You'll see the Ollama icon in the menu bar

Method 2: Using Homebrew
bash# Install Homebrew if you don't have it
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

# Install Ollama
brew install ollama
Download the AI Model:
bash# Open a new terminal (keep the first one open!)
# In the new terminal:

# Download phi3 model
ollama pull phi3

# Verify it downloaded
ollama list

# Start Ollama service (if not already running)
ollama serve
Step 6: Run the Application
bash# Back in the first terminal (where virtual environment is activated)
cd ~/Desktop/AI_andreas

# Make sure environment is activated (you should see (venv) in prompt)
# If not activated:
source venv/bin/activate

# Run the application
streamlit run AI_andreas.py
Step 7: Access the Application

Browser will automatically open at http://localhost:8501
If it doesn't open automatically, manually navigate to this address


